You had been asking me
to do x-ray, CT scan,

46
00:03:54,839 --> 00:03:56,479
blood test, urine test,
tumour screening.

47
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,279
Those who involved know that I hurt my arm.

48
00:03:58,439 --> 00:04:01,400
And those who didn't will think
that I'm in serious condition.

49
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,639
You finally came to a hospital.

50
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,960
Of course you need to do
all kinds of tests there are.

51
00:04:06,199 --> 00:04:07,639
There's a time limit.

52
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,160
If you have a sequela later,

53
00:04:09,279 --> 00:04:11,120
I won't take the responsibility for it.

54
00:04:11,279 --> 00:04:12,120
Excuse me.

55
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,800
I have a question.

56
00:04:13,999 --> 00:04:14,999
Ask.

57
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,479
Why do I have to come
to the sterile ward...

58
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,680
from a hand wound.

59
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:22,759
Should I stay in the corridor...

60
00:04:22,879 --> 00:04:25,479
and be with those people who are ill?

61
00:04:26,079 --> 00:04:27,560
You can stay out then.

62
00:04:27,759 --> 00:04:30,039
Do you think I want to come?
If it isn't because...

63
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,800
Is something wrong with you?

64
00:04:35,919 --> 00:04:36,919
My arm.

65
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:39,520
Does a wounded arm counts?

66
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,079
I'm not talking about this.

67
00:04:41,319 --> 00:04:42,560
What I mean is,

68
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,560
who do you think you are?

69
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:47,159
Why did you drag yourself
into my fight?

70
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,680
Did I ask you or beg you...

71
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,359
to take that hit for me?

72
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:54,000
Tell me the reason.
Why did you do that?

73
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:56,240
I just helped because I was there.

74
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,840
What's wrong with that?

75
00:04:57,960 --> 00:05:00,599
Am I supposed to stand aside
while they hit you?

76
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,319
I don't like to be in debt with others.

77
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,159
I don't have much cash with me.

78
00:05:06,319 --> 00:05:07,479
Take these first.

79
00:05:08,199 --> 00:05:10,599
And then, tell me your
bank account number.

80
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,199
I'll ask my assistant to
transfer money to you.

81
00:05:12,359 --> 00:05:13,639
I don't want your money.

82
00:05:14,359 --> 00:05:16,079
My body is priceless.

83
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:18,359
I don't plan to get rich with it.

84
00:05:19,879 --> 00:05:20,879
Fine.

85
00:05:21,359 --> 00:05:22,560
Tell me then.

86
00:05:22,759 --> 00:05:24,079
Do you have anything you want?

87
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:27,240
Something that can be realised quickly.
You can't leave until you tell me.

88
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:30,520
You are so unreasonable.

89
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:32,240
Then,

90
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:34,479
I want to get into the postgraduate.

91
00:05:35,159 --> 00:05:36,879
It needs at least one year.

92
00:05:37,039 --> 00:05:39,000
Do you know what short-term means?

93
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:43,240
Short-term? If that's the case...

94
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,599
I want to pass my Art Theory.

95
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:50,560
-That's it?
-It's very hard.

96
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:53,720
Art History and Introduction to Art
are so hard to memorise.

97
00:05:53,879 --> 00:05:56,639
I'll be very thankful if I can
pass just either of them.

98
00:05:58,199 --> 00:06:00,000
Fine, I got it.

99
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:02,039
What do you mean by that?

100
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,919
You can help me with it?
How are you going to help?

101
00:06:05,039 --> 00:06:07,280
Just shut up and wait.

102
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,759
Zhou Shi, what happened to your hand?

103
00:06:31,919 --> 00:06:34,359
It was still fine yesterday.
How did it...

104
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:35,800
I'm fine.

105
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,199
-How did you get hurt?
-From a fight.

106
00:06:39,919 --> 00:06:42,759
You can consider it as heroic.

107
00:06:43,079 --> 00:06:45,840
No, I think it should be called
brave act for a just cause.

108
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:48,840
So, your hand turns out like this?

109
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,720
More or less like that.

110
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,039
I already told you.

111
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:54,800
You shouldn't work
at that kind of place.

112
00:06:54,919 --> 00:06:56,359
He's not worth your saving.

113
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,919
If you want to earn money,
I'll recommend works to you.

114
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:01,240
Easy works where you
don't have to put yourself out there.

115
00:07:02,599 --> 00:07:03,560
Zhou Shi.

116
00:07:04,039 --> 00:07:05,199
Are you listening?

117
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:09,240
I'm so sleepy. Who's the one
giving the lecture today?

118
00:07:09,879 --> 00:07:12,560
I don't know. The university had kept it
to themselves quite well.

119
00:07:12,759 --> 00:07:14,199
I think it might be a famous person.

120
00:07:17,159 --> 00:07:18,759
What a big lecture.

121
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,720
I don't care. Nothing can
stop me from sleeping...

122
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,240
even if he's the best actor.

123
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,280
I didn't really sleep at all yesterday.

124
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,879
Let me take a nap first.

125
00:07:42,919 --> 00:07:44,720
Hello. We all know that...

126
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:45,879
your family...

127
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,280
started from operating art gallery.

128
00:07:48,479 --> 00:07:50,440
Like many of the students
from our university,

129
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:53,159
a lot of the young artists wish
to sign up with an art gallery...

130
00:07:53,159 --> 00:07:54,520
as soon as they graduate.

131
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:56,079
What suggestions can you give...

132
00:07:56,199 --> 00:07:57,919
to students like that?

133
00:08:02,199 --> 00:08:03,840
As the manager of an art gallery,

134
00:08:04,039 --> 00:08:07,680
the first thing to consider is how to
improve the brand value of the gallery.

135
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:18,280
You shouldn't just hope that
you can improve your own value...

136
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:20,280
by joining certain art gallery.

137
00:08:21,199 --> 00:08:22,400
Thank you very much.

138
00:08:22,599 --> 00:08:24,039
Now, it's time for...

139
00:08:24,159 --> 00:08:25,720
the awaited Q&A session.

140
00:08:25,879 --> 00:08:27,680
Do you have any questions?

141
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,159
Such enthusiasm.

142
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:34,159
Let us hear this lady
in yellow coat...

143
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:36,479
who is putting both of her hands up.

144
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,399
Please pass the microphone to her.

145
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,640
What is happening now?

146
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:50,240
Do you have any questions
for Chairman Wei?

147
00:08:53,889 --> 00:08:56,628
[What to eat for lunch?]
[Any comments on the new artists now?]

148
00:08:56,719 --> 00:08:58,200
What to eat for lunch?

149
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:03,479
It should be the one below it.

150
00:09:19,599 --> 00:09:21,279
Apologise to Chairman Wei properly.

151
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,760
Do you know how much effort we put in...

152
00:09:24,959 --> 00:09:27,680
to invite Chairman Wei
to be our guest professor?

153
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:31,120
What did you do?
You slept in the class.

154
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,919
There should be a limit...

155
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,839
