156
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,479
Professor.

157
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:39,479
Is him here for business?

158
00:09:39,719 --> 00:09:40,959
What would you know?

159
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:43,279
With Wei family's reputation
in the world of collectors...

160
00:09:43,479 --> 00:09:44,760
and his father,

161
00:09:44,919 --> 00:09:46,760
Wei Heng's achievement in oil painting,

162
00:09:46,959 --> 00:09:49,479
just a few words from him
in a lecture...

163
00:09:49,719 --> 00:09:52,039
will boost the sales for the
next issue of art magazines.

164
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:53,159
Understood?

165
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,279
Moreover, Chairman Wei...

166
00:09:55,279 --> 00:09:57,440
is a professor who graduated
from Royal College of Art.

167
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:59,359
He is qualified to teach you.

168
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:02,240
Cut the nonsense.
Apologise to him now.

169
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:12,240
Old Yan, I have something to say to her.

170
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:14,240
-Continue with your work.
-Alright.

171
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:16,760
Apologise to him properly.

172
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:24,640
-What are you doing?
-Apologising.

173
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,519
How rigid. Compared to an apology,

174
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:29,479
I rather hope that I can talk to you...

175
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:31,800
about what to eat for lunch today.

176
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,320
Is your company so free?

177
00:10:34,479 --> 00:10:35,680
Why would you have the time...

178
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,640
to be a professor in our university?

179
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:38,719
I'm here...

180
00:10:39,519 --> 00:10:40,719
to repay my gratitude.

181
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:42,039
What?

182
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:45,080
Last night, you said that you want
to pass your theory exam, right?

183
00:10:45,279 --> 00:10:46,800
I've seen your results.

184
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,880
Your Introduction to Art subject
is the worst.

185
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:51,039
And next is History of Art.

186
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:54,000
Basically, you hover on the line
between passing and failing.

187
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,080
Old Yan had introduced me just now.

188
00:10:56,279 --> 00:10:59,000
I don't know about other things.
But I'm qualified enough to...

189
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,440
teach you about art theories.

190
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:02,599
It wouldn't hurt to call me a teacher.

191
00:11:04,519 --> 00:11:05,719
Are you saying that...

192
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,519
you can help me pass the test?

193
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:09,919
Then what should I do?

194
00:11:13,719 --> 00:11:16,959
Do the PowerPoint for
our lecture tomorrow.

195
00:11:17,159 --> 00:11:18,359
What is this?

196
00:11:18,519 --> 00:11:22,279
The topic, context and reference books
are already listed here in details.

197
00:11:22,479 --> 00:11:23,919
Get it done by tomorrow morning.

198
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:26,320
Or else, you'll have
to take the responsibility...

199
00:11:26,599 --> 00:11:27,719
for a blank PowerPoint.

200
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:31,159
-I won't do it.
-No choice. This is your assignment.

201
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,719
Why are you like this?

202
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,320
It's fine if you don't want to do it.

203
00:11:34,479 --> 00:11:37,440
I can just tell Old Yan about you
working part-time in a bar.

204
00:11:38,959 --> 00:11:40,839
You are ruthless.

205
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,479
Why are you still standing over here?

206
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:48,880
The library will close on five.

207
00:11:49,719 --> 00:11:52,159
Go ahead and waste
your time here if you want.

208
00:12:05,159 --> 00:12:08,120
So much information.
And I have to memorise it in a night.

209
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,200
Is this how you repay for kindness?

210
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:13,200
I should have just rescued
a husky instead.

211
00:12:13,959 --> 00:12:15,479
I'm too unlucky.

212
00:12:22,959 --> 00:12:24,159
Gao Yang?

213
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,680
Tell me clearly.
What happened to Fei Fei?

214
00:12:28,519 --> 00:12:31,080
Bowl? What bowl?

215
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,760
Stop mentioning bowl.

216
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:35,080
Now, I'm surrounded
by bowls everywhere.

217
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:37,039
Starting from last night,

218
00:12:37,279 --> 00:12:40,359
Lin Fei Fei has been buying bowls
like a possessed woman.

219
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,880
I already max out one of my cards.

220
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,919
If this continues,

221
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
my parents will cut my sub-card.

222
00:12:46,519 --> 00:12:47,880
Why are there so many bowls?

223
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,279
My vision are already blurred
from picking them out.

224
00:12:49,399 --> 00:12:50,440
Your eyes are black.

225
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:51,800
Black?

226
00:12:52,479 --> 00:12:53,599
What about this?

227
00:12:56,279 --> 00:12:58,159
Does this look like the broken bowl?

228
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,599
I'll stop now.

229
00:12:59,760 --> 00:13:02,240
Please talk to your friends.
I'll be leaving now.

230
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:04,599
Don't go! If you leave, what she would do?

231
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:07,680
How can you be like that?

232
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:09,399
Please be decisive.

233
00:13:09,519 --> 00:13:12,359
This is already the tenth bowl that
you think is similar to it.

234
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:16,479
Have you made a decision
about your choice?

235
00:13:17,039 --> 00:13:17,880
Wait for a moment.

236
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,519
Gao Yang.

237
00:13:23,519 --> 00:13:25,159
Where are you going, you jerk.

238
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,880
Fei Fei!

239
00:13:34,279 --> 00:13:36,359
Why are you so loud? You scared me.

240
00:13:36,479 --> 00:13:38,080
-What is it?
-Have you paid?

241
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:39,200
No.

242
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,440
Good. Listen to me.

243
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:42,440
Put them back. Don't buy them.

244
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,599
No.

245
00:13:44,479 --> 00:13:45,719
Can you stop?

246
00:13:45,839 --> 00:13:47,200
Why do you need so many bowls?

247
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:48,800
To open a shop, for exhibition...

248
00:13:48,959 --> 00:13:50,880
or to summon God and dragon
from your collection?

249
00:13:51,359 --> 00:13:53,479
No. I don't care.
I won't stop until I got it.

250
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:55,800
I have to show the boy upstairs
that I'm better even if...

251
00:13:55,919 --> 00:13:57,359
I have to cut off my hands tomorrow.

252
00:13:57,519 --> 00:13:58,959
Why the enmity?

253
00:13:59,120 --> 00:14:00,640
What happened between you both?

254
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,039
No. I'm telling you that...

255
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:06,159
Let me speak. It's like this.

256
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:12,159
Open the door.

257
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:24,640
This is for you.
I don't like to owe someone.

258
00:14:24,839 --> 00:14:26,399
I said that I'll pay you back.

259
00:14:26,599 --> 00:14:28,279
I've searched all the shops around me.

260
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:29,800
This is the most similar one.

261
00:14:29,959 --> 00:14:32,039
It's yours now. Don't say that
I took advantage of you.

262
00:14:39,039 --> 00:14:40,159
Are you insane?

263
00:14:40,279 --> 00:14:42,000
Don't drop it even if you don't want it.

264
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,320
Fine. You don't want a bowl, right?

